WEBVTT

00:08.367 --> 00:12.166
For those of you
who are too fucking busy,

00:12.166 --> 00:14.200
this is what happened
last week on  Shameless.

00:14.200 --> 00:15.133
I left them.

00:15.133 --> 00:17.133
Get fucked!

00:18.567 --> 00:20.000
This your home now?

00:20.000 --> 00:21.533
First time in my life
I ever felt like

00:21.533 --> 00:23.100
I actually belonged somewhere.

00:23.100 --> 00:25.266
What's it like with my dad
living at your house?

00:25.266 --> 00:27.266
Weird.
It's only going
to get weirder.

00:28.300 --> 00:30.233
Last night was
my first time.

00:30.233 --> 00:31.367
You mean your
first time with me.

00:31.367 --> 00:32.633
Virgin?
Yep.

00:32.633 --> 00:34.367
Aunt Ginger has to go back?

00:34.367 --> 00:35.633
Don't make her go.

00:35.633 --> 00:36.734
She doesn't belong to us.

00:36.734 --> 00:38.266
Old guy next door died in March,

00:38.266 --> 00:40.567
which I guess, technically,
makes us next-door neighbors!

00:40.567 --> 00:42.000
Where's my damn toaster?

00:42.000 --> 00:45.000
Leave me alone!
You would not
be so pissed off

00:45.000 --> 00:45.734
if you didn't care.

00:45.734 --> 00:46.667
When I saw the
way you looked

00:46.667 --> 00:48.433
at Steve,
like a D-O-G in heat.

00:48.433 --> 00:49.667
My mom heard about it.

00:49.667 --> 00:51.533
She invited you to dinner.

00:53.300 --> 00:54.300
Hi.

01:03.300 --> 01:05.467
("The Luck You Got"
by The High Strung beings)

01:10.300 --> 01:13.600
♪ Think of all
the luck you got ♪

01:13.600 --> 01:16.767
♪ Know that it's not
for naught ♪

01:16.767 --> 01:20.000
♪ You were beaming once before ♪

01:20.000 --> 01:24.166
♪ But it's not like that
anymore ♪

01:24.166 --> 01:27.567
♪ What is this downside ♪

01:27.567 --> 01:31.100
♪ That you speak of? ♪

01:31.100 --> 01:37.700
♪ What is this feeling
you're so sure of? ♪

01:44.767 --> 01:48.033
♪ Round up the friends you got ♪

01:48.033 --> 01:51.333
♪ Know that they're
not for naught ♪

01:51.333 --> 01:54.633
♪ You were willing once before ♪

01:54.633 --> 01:58.567
♪ But it's not like that
anymore ♪

01:58.567 --> 02:02.000
♪ What is this downside ♪

02:02.000 --> 02:05.700
♪ That you speak of? ♪

02:05.700 --> 02:08.066
♪ What is this feeling ♪

02:08.066 --> 02:11.233
♪ You're so... sure of? ♪

02:17.266 --> 02:19.667
Aw.

02:19.667 --> 02:21.400
Sweet little baby.

02:21.400 --> 02:23.533
Scarf on...

02:23.533 --> 02:25.000
(humming happily)

02:30.767 --> 02:32.700
Debbie, come in and eat
your breakfast, okay?

02:32.700 --> 02:34.433
You're up next
in the shower.

02:34.433 --> 02:35.767
I want to play
for a while.

02:35.767 --> 02:38.066
Ask Carl if he'll come out
and get in the stroller.

02:38.066 --> 02:39.266
The last time
you asked Carl to play,

02:39.266 --> 02:40.667
you were locked in
the basement for half a day.

02:40.667 --> 02:42.200
That was on purpose.

02:42.200 --> 02:43.667
And we were playing
"Loser Goes to Gitmo."

02:43.667 --> 02:46.400
FIONA: Let's go! And put that
stroller back in the garbage.

02:52.100 --> 02:54.166
(metal creaking)

02:59.033 --> 03:01.166
Oh, man, yeah...
that's, uh, it's dead.

03:01.166 --> 03:02.667
You sure?
Uh-huh.

03:02.667 --> 03:04.233
The element's
rusted out.

03:04.233 --> 03:06.333
Anyone want to make some
Tollhouse cookies with me?

03:06.333 --> 03:07.500
How much to replace it?

03:07.500 --> 03:09.233
Uh, two bills
used, four new.

03:09.233 --> 03:10.367
FIONA:
Shit.

03:10.367 --> 03:11.500
How about a pie?

03:11.500 --> 03:13.033
I can get started
on the crust.

03:13.033 --> 03:14.367
Go take your shower.

03:14.367 --> 03:17.233
I... wanna... make... pie.

03:17.233 --> 03:18.667
You know what?
Hand me the obits.

03:18.667 --> 03:21.233
Maybe, uh, we can scrounge
a dead person's water heater.

03:21.233 --> 03:22.633
Thank you.

03:22.633 --> 03:24.166
Ah, Mrs. Dombrowski.

03:24.166 --> 03:26.100
Oh, the, uh,
shaky neck lady?

03:26.100 --> 03:28.233
I thought she drowned
a couple years ago.

03:28.233 --> 03:30.467
DEBBIE: No. Mrs. Goga
had the shaky neck,

03:30.467 --> 03:33.166
and she drowned in her
own vomit last Easter.

03:33.166 --> 03:35.600
No pie. Get in the shower.
I'm not saying it again.

03:35.600 --> 03:36.700
Carl, no.

03:36.700 --> 03:40.033
I went to school
with Kenny Dombrowski.

03:40.033 --> 03:41.400
Think he had
a crush on me.

03:41.400 --> 03:42.700
Her wake's this morning.
Let's go.

03:42.700 --> 03:44.100
Mm.
Up, up, up.

03:44.100 --> 03:45.233
Can I come?

03:45.233 --> 03:48.400
Um... no.

03:48.400 --> 03:50.300
Debbie, what is
going on with you?

03:52.200 --> 03:53.533
Nothing.

03:53.533 --> 03:56.000
(Fiona sighs with frustration)

03:58.133 --> 03:58.767
(inhales)

03:58.767 --> 04:00.266
Oof. Shower.

04:00.266 --> 04:01.333
After Debbie.

04:01.333 --> 04:03.633
Towel and robe,
upstairs. Go.

04:03.633 --> 04:05.400
(Liam jabbers)

04:05.400 --> 04:07.467
And you need to learn how
to change your own diaper.

04:25.700 --> 04:27.033
(people talking outside)

04:28.333 --> 04:30.700
MAN: All right, it's
getting kind of windy.

04:30.700 --> 04:34.033
Beautiful day for a party!

04:34.033 --> 04:35.567
MAN: It's for kids, Frank!
No booze!

04:38.667 --> 04:40.033
(quietly):
Son of a...

04:41.734 --> 04:43.233
Oh...

04:43.233 --> 04:45.667
How would you like
your eggs, sweetie?

04:45.667 --> 04:47.734
Fluffy.
Oh.

04:50.166 --> 04:52.567
They're having a party
across the street.

04:52.567 --> 04:54.467
What, dear?

04:54.467 --> 04:55.767
Across the street.

04:55.767 --> 04:57.533
Some sort of
a party for kids.

04:57.533 --> 04:59.467
No booze.

04:59.467 --> 05:01.633
What's the point?

05:01.633 --> 05:04.734
♪ ♪

05:13.300 --> 05:14.533
Dad?

05:28.266 --> 05:31.400
KAREN:
What the hell is he doing here?

05:33.600 --> 05:35.333
(laughing)

05:35.333 --> 05:37.233
(heavy breathing)

05:37.233 --> 05:38.367
Debbie?

05:38.367 --> 05:40.233
What?
What?
Stay focused, baby.

05:40.233 --> 05:42.200
Are the Gallaghers
in our bathroom?

05:42.200 --> 05:44.400
Oh, I know what
you need, huh?

05:44.400 --> 05:45.667
Huh?
Uh-huh.

05:45.667 --> 05:47.000
Uh-huh.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.367
Want some...
Yeah? Mm-hmm.

05:51.767 --> 05:53.734
(kissing)

05:53.734 --> 05:54.500
Ooh...

06:14.767 --> 06:16.600
All right,
they're ready.
Aha.

06:16.600 --> 06:19.734
Fluffy, fluffy,
floo-floo.

06:24.767 --> 06:26.533
Went to see
a lawyer.

06:26.533 --> 06:29.133
It turns out I can't afford
to live somewhere else

06:29.133 --> 06:31.400
and support you two.

06:31.400 --> 06:32.767
Three.

06:32.767 --> 06:34.300
Why can't you stay
with Uncle Ray?

06:34.300 --> 06:35.767
He's got gangrene.

06:35.767 --> 06:37.266
You ever smell
a rotting foot?

06:37.266 --> 06:38.667
Hey.

06:38.667 --> 06:41.367
Why don't you get me a refill
there, huh, Karen, honey?

06:41.367 --> 06:43.133
What, did you lose
your fucking legs?

06:43.133 --> 06:45.300
Yeah, that's your teenage,
diseased mind talking.

06:45.300 --> 06:48.000
EDDIE:
You know, you tasted penii,

06:48.000 --> 06:49.533
and now you're
just crazy.

06:49.533 --> 06:51.133
(coughing)

07:03.200 --> 07:05.300
(funky intro begins)

07:12.600 --> 07:15.000
♪ It's hotter,
it's sweeter ♪

07:15.000 --> 07:17.266
♪ It's hotter, it's sweeter ♪

07:17.266 --> 07:19.233
♪ Hotter, sweeter ♪

07:19.233 --> 07:22.066
♪ Hotter,
sweeter ♪

07:22.066 --> 07:23.233
♪ Hotter, sweeter ♪

07:23.233 --> 07:25.433
♪ Hotter,
sweeter ♪

07:25.433 --> 07:27.333
(shower running)

07:30.633 --> 07:32.500
(flushes)

07:37.033 --> 07:38.667
(screams)

07:38.667 --> 07:42.033
Oh, shit! That's cold!

07:42.033 --> 07:44.066
What the hell? Veronica!

07:44.066 --> 07:45.500
There's no hot water.

07:49.033 --> 07:51.433
What?

07:51.433 --> 07:53.367
Fucking Gallaghers!

07:56.734 --> 07:58.667
Well, look at you, just letting
yourself into people's houses.

07:58.667 --> 08:00.734
Tall grande latte,
two shots.

08:00.734 --> 08:02.200
Sugar?
Absolutely.

08:03.767 --> 08:05.633
Kids home?

08:05.633 --> 08:07.066
Mm...

08:07.066 --> 08:08.333
Boys're out getting
a water heater,

08:08.333 --> 08:09.633
Debbie's at the park,

08:09.633 --> 08:13.166
Carl's out looking for small
defenseless pets to torture,

08:13.166 --> 08:14.700
and Liam's down for a nap.

08:14.700 --> 08:15.600
So...

08:15.600 --> 08:17.066
No.

08:17.066 --> 08:18.133
I'm up to my ass
in housework.

08:18.133 --> 08:19.367
That's why I'm taking you to

08:19.367 --> 08:21.033
a long, deep, leisurely lunch.

08:21.033 --> 08:22.100
Lunch?

08:22.100 --> 08:23.066
It's a euphemism.

08:23.066 --> 08:25.367
How quaint.

08:25.367 --> 08:27.533
Or, would you like a Demon dog
and a quick fuck

08:27.533 --> 08:29.233
over at the Sheridan?

08:29.233 --> 08:30.300
Liam?
Get a sitter.

08:30.300 --> 08:31.767
Costs too much.

08:31.767 --> 08:33.633
How much?

08:33.633 --> 08:35.100
At least 50 bucks.

08:37.233 --> 08:38.700
You're not paying me
to fuck you.

08:38.700 --> 08:40.367
No, I couldn't
pay you enough.

08:43.667 --> 08:45.633
(distant thud)

08:45.633 --> 08:46.700
Did you hear that?

08:46.700 --> 08:48.633
No.

08:48.633 --> 08:50.200
You didn't hear that?

08:50.200 --> 08:51.667
You trying to
change the subject?

08:51.667 --> 08:53.400
(thudding)

08:54.467 --> 08:55.700
Liam?

08:55.700 --> 08:58.400
He's too lazy to get out of
his crib-- he just yells.

09:01.500 --> 09:03.533
(thudding)

09:03.533 --> 09:05.567
You stay with Liam.
Wait, wait, wait...

09:08.667 --> 09:10.667
(whispering): You take
the baby, I'll take the bat.

09:11.734 --> 09:13.667
(whispers indistinctly)

09:28.033 --> 09:29.000
(clattering)

09:33.300 --> 09:35.734
Debbie! Jesus!

09:35.734 --> 09:37.667
Thought you went
to the park.

09:37.667 --> 09:39.367
I... came back.

09:39.367 --> 09:41.300
Are you okay?

09:41.300 --> 09:45.033
Katie Crasden's
having a party.

09:45.033 --> 09:46.433
Katie Crasden?

09:46.433 --> 09:48.433
Two streets over.

09:48.433 --> 09:50.467
STEVE: And she...
didn't invite you?

09:50.467 --> 09:52.000
She's only three.

09:52.000 --> 09:53.333
What happened?

09:53.333 --> 09:57.166
Well, I was just walking past,

09:57.166 --> 09:58.500
and her dad, he...

09:59.300 --> 10:01.467
Her dad did what?

10:01.467 --> 10:05.166
He was laughing and playing
with them, and it just...

10:05.166 --> 10:06.667
it wasn't fair.

10:06.667 --> 10:09.400
What wasn't fair? What?

10:09.400 --> 10:11.333
Everything.

10:11.333 --> 10:12.767
So I, I, um...

10:14.767 --> 10:17.233
I stole something.

10:17.233 --> 10:18.567
Oh...
(sighs)

10:18.567 --> 10:20.033
So nobody touched you?

10:20.033 --> 10:21.266
What?

10:21.266 --> 10:22.567
You nearly gave me
a heart attack.

10:22.567 --> 10:25.333
TODDLER:
A bike.

10:27.033 --> 10:30.033
TODDLER:
Race car... don't hit the train!

10:30.033 --> 10:31.767
Debbie?

10:34.467 --> 10:36.133
(giggles)

10:36.133 --> 10:38.066
Who the hell is that?

10:38.467 --> 10:41.233
(siren wailing)

10:44.000 --> 10:46.033
WOMAN: We'll all be...
we'll just organize.

10:46.033 --> 10:47.000
We'll be okay.

10:47.000 --> 10:48.734
(sirens approaching)

10:52.467 --> 10:54.567
(sirens stop)
MAN: Just relax.

10:54.567 --> 10:56.600
Oh, here we go!

10:56.600 --> 11:00.200
No traffic tickets
to issue today?

11:00.200 --> 11:05.200
No one to pull over for swinging
wide on a left-hand turn?

11:05.200 --> 11:09.133
Or is this a supportive
"friend party" for a cop

11:09.133 --> 11:11.700
who shot some poor fucker
wasn't even armed?!

11:11.700 --> 11:13.500
Leave the people
around here alone.

11:13.500 --> 11:14.600
They're good folks!

11:14.600 --> 11:15.767
Who are the parents?

11:15.767 --> 11:17.433
Let's go, people.
Out of the way.

11:17.433 --> 11:18.433
Your child's missing?

11:18.433 --> 11:20.000
MAN:
Yeah.
I need your names

11:20.000 --> 11:22.100
and the name
of the child.

11:22.100 --> 11:24.467
Beth and Gary Casden.

11:24.467 --> 11:27.300
Mr. and Mrs. Casden, when is
the last time you saw...?
Uh, Ca-Casey.

11:27.300 --> 11:28.433
It's been
about an hour ago.

11:28.433 --> 11:31.333
Okay, okay.
What was he wearing?

11:31.333 --> 11:32.500
(chuckles)

11:32.500 --> 11:34.700
Debbie, why would
you steal

11:34.700 --> 11:37.533
a little girl?

11:37.533 --> 11:39.266
Why would you steal a little boy

11:39.266 --> 11:40.567
and dress him
like a little girl?

11:40.567 --> 11:42.367
(speaks indistinctly, laughs)

11:42.367 --> 11:44.633
I wanted a girl,
but there weren't any.

11:44.633 --> 11:46.767
Then back
to my initial question:

11:46.767 --> 11:48.500
Why would you steal
a baby at all?

11:48.500 --> 11:50.033
I miss Ginger.

11:50.033 --> 11:51.300
What?
Who?

11:51.300 --> 11:53.033
You took away Aunt Ginger!

11:53.033 --> 11:54.200
Who is Aunt Ginger?

11:54.200 --> 11:56.133
Somebody we borrowed
from V's nursing home.

11:56.133 --> 11:57.300
What?

11:57.300 --> 11:58.467
She was my friend.

11:58.467 --> 12:01.233
We have to take him back
right away, okay?

12:01.233 --> 12:02.367
Where are
his boy clothes?

12:02.367 --> 12:04.600
I washed them.

12:06.533 --> 12:08.233
Oh, my God, it shrunk!

12:08.233 --> 12:09.533
You put it in the dryer?

12:09.533 --> 12:11.533
That's what you do
after you wash something.

12:11.533 --> 12:14.567
Um, we can put him in
some of Liam clothes.

12:14.567 --> 12:17.166
We can't bring
a missing kid back

12:17.166 --> 12:18.333
wearing different
clothes.

12:18.333 --> 12:20.500
People will say
we did something to him.

12:20.500 --> 12:22.033
Something bad.

12:24.567 --> 12:26.266
MIKE (over P.A.):
Attention: This is...

12:26.266 --> 12:27.433
Attention:
This is the Chicago...

12:27.433 --> 12:29.467
Push, then...
I know what to push.

12:29.467 --> 12:30.533
Attention!
This is the Chicago...

12:30.533 --> 12:32.133
No. All right.
What are you doing?

12:32.133 --> 12:33.700
Mike, we have to get
the information out.

12:33.700 --> 12:35.567
Then let me drive.
No.

12:35.567 --> 12:38.467
Look, I've been a cop
a lot longer than you.

12:38.467 --> 12:41.033
You don't get to drive
and talk on the loudspeaker.

12:41.033 --> 12:42.633
What, are you gonna
call your uncle?

12:42.633 --> 12:45.166
Attention: This is the Chicago
Police Department.

12:45.166 --> 12:47.133
We're looking for a missing
two-year-old...

12:47.133 --> 12:49.767
IAN: So we're just
gonna wait out here?

12:49.767 --> 12:51.433
He's a chain-smoking
pothead in

12:51.433 --> 12:54.400
a stress-inducing situation;
he'll be out soon.

12:54.400 --> 12:56.567
What are we
supposed to say?

12:56.567 --> 12:58.166
I don't know.
Just play it cool.

12:58.166 --> 12:59.567
Play what cool?

12:59.567 --> 13:02.400
Things people play cool.
Jesus, Ian!

13:02.400 --> 13:03.533
(phone rings)

13:03.533 --> 13:05.300
You got your own cell?

13:05.300 --> 13:08.233
No, some kid left it in
the cafeteria.
Ah.

13:08.233 --> 13:10.166
Hey, Kare.

13:10.166 --> 13:11.700
Yeah, I'm at some
dead lady's house

13:11.700 --> 13:13.734
trying to see if I can
score a water heater.

13:13.734 --> 13:14.600
Meet me after?

13:14.600 --> 13:16.767
FIONA:
Hey, V?!

13:16.767 --> 13:18.500
I'm in the bathroom!

13:18.500 --> 13:20.500
Hey, I'm in a bit of a jam.

13:20.500 --> 13:21.734
Can you watch him
for 15 minutes?

13:21.734 --> 13:24.300
Damn, Fi, you see I'm in
the middle of doing my--

13:24.300 --> 13:25.633
Thanks.
Okay, sure.

13:28.266 --> 13:29.333
Hey, Li...!

13:31.033 --> 13:32.400
Who the fuck are you?

13:34.767 --> 13:38.233
(siren approaching)

13:38.233 --> 13:39.533
Oh, shit!

13:43.266 --> 13:44.133
Hey, Fiona.

13:44.133 --> 13:45.333
Hey, Tony.

13:45.333 --> 13:47.400
You remember Steve?

13:47.400 --> 13:49.100
Yeah. How's it going?

13:49.100 --> 13:50.734
Uh, hear about the missing boy?

13:50.734 --> 13:52.066
No. What happened?

13:52.066 --> 13:54.000
Got taken from a front yard
birthday party.

13:54.000 --> 13:56.100
Do they think he might have
just wandered off?

13:56.100 --> 13:57.500
We've got everybody out looking:

13:57.500 --> 14:00.300
choppers, SWAT, couple dozen
extra units, Amber alerts.

14:00.300 --> 14:02.200
Wow. Really.

14:02.200 --> 14:04.433
We're gonna catch the bastard
that took little Casey

14:04.433 --> 14:06.433
and chop his pedophile nuts off.

14:07.633 --> 14:10.000
(helicopter passes,
siren wails)

14:12.166 --> 14:15.533
Less than two hours ago, a young
boy, only two years of age,

14:15.533 --> 14:17.734
was abducted
from his front yard.

14:17.734 --> 14:19.066
You see this?

14:19.066 --> 14:21.433
This is what happens
when the world goes crazy.

14:21.433 --> 14:23.567
People steal kids.

14:23.567 --> 14:26.500
And Rastafarians
are allowed to roam free.

14:26.500 --> 14:28.266
I don't mean real Rastafarians.

14:28.266 --> 14:31.200
I mean Rastaman Goldberg's
from Lake Forest

14:31.200 --> 14:34.633
with rich parents who get
dropped off in Town Cars

14:34.633 --> 14:37.333
to go beg for money on
the streets.

14:37.333 --> 14:38.333
What a load of crap.

14:38.333 --> 14:39.600
Obamacare, my ass!

14:39.600 --> 14:41.533
What the news people
don't tell you?

14:41.533 --> 14:45.700
They love it
when kids get stolen.

14:45.700 --> 14:47.533
They're just looking
for a good story

14:47.533 --> 14:50.033
to saturate our airwaves with.

14:50.033 --> 14:52.500
And why are all
the news ladies Chinese?

14:52.500 --> 14:55.100
They should stick
to what they know:

14:55.100 --> 15:00.300
railroads... sushi...
dim sum.

15:00.300 --> 15:02.367
Frank, guess what.

15:02.367 --> 15:06.533
I made muffins using
a Bundt cake batter.

15:06.533 --> 15:09.333
I didn't even need
to add another egg.

15:09.333 --> 15:10.367
(chuckles)

15:10.367 --> 15:12.033
Hi, sweetie.

15:12.033 --> 15:13.033
The shithead gone?

15:13.033 --> 15:14.400
He just left for work.

15:14.400 --> 15:15.467
EDDIE:
I'm still here.

15:15.467 --> 15:17.367
Just getting my coat.

15:17.367 --> 15:19.633
