(sirens wailing in distance)

27:47.066 --> 27:49.133
ANCHORWOMAN: In just a moment,
we will take you live

27:49.133 --> 27:50.533
to the scene of the crime,

27:50.533 --> 27:53.166
with our field correspondent
Charles Catino.

27:53.166 --> 27:55.500
But first,
if you have any information

27:55.500 --> 27:57.633
regarding the whereabouts
of Casey Casden,

27:57.633 --> 28:00.500
please call the number
at the bottom of your screen.

28:00.500 --> 28:01.433
Charles, are you there?

28:01.433 --> 28:03.533
(women laughing loudly)

28:03.533 --> 28:05.767
(laughing, screaming)

28:05.767 --> 28:07.667
Shots on me!

28:10.367 --> 28:11.500
You are soaking wet!

28:14.400 --> 28:16.567
(women laughing,
squealing)

28:19.767 --> 28:22.033
(stammering)

28:22.033 --> 28:25.100
Uh, so... fixing up
the basement.

28:25.100 --> 28:26.367
Mm-hmm. Gonna try.

28:26.367 --> 28:28.633
Sheetrock that corner
space for my bed.

28:28.633 --> 28:31.667
The other half's already
paneled, so I'm good there.

28:31.667 --> 28:34.433
Got a spot for the sink;
toilet's already in.

28:34.433 --> 28:39.266
So, just run some cable for the
flat-screen, and I'm all set.

28:39.266 --> 28:42.400
So...

28:42.400 --> 28:45.500
that Sheila,
she's something, huh?

28:45.500 --> 28:48.166
That's one way to put it.

28:50.266 --> 28:52.133
Does your ass
ever stop hurting?

28:52.133 --> 28:55.300
No.

28:55.300 --> 28:56.600
Advil's your best bet.

28:56.600 --> 28:58.667
Helps with the
inflammation.

29:00.266 --> 29:02.100
Hey, Kev.

29:02.100 --> 29:03.567
Hey.
You see my friend?

29:03.567 --> 29:06.400
I know she acts like she hits
on everyone, but she's doesn't.

29:06.400 --> 29:08.533
She likes you.

29:08.533 --> 29:10.500
Well, I'm flattered,
but I can't.

29:10.500 --> 29:12.734
Kev, you wanna get to it?

29:12.734 --> 29:14.500
Oh, come on, what can
one little drink hurt?

29:14.500 --> 29:15.500
Um, uh...

29:15.500 --> 29:18.166
yeah... really, no.

29:18.166 --> 29:20.633
Look, she doesn't care
if you have a girlfriend.

29:20.633 --> 29:22.500
Neither do I.

29:22.500 --> 29:25.734
Can you handle two?

29:28.433 --> 29:29.633
What, the both of you?

29:31.266 --> 29:32.734
(clears throat)

29:32.734 --> 29:34.567
Uh, I can't, really.

29:34.567 --> 29:37.734
Actually, um...
I'm getting married.

29:37.734 --> 29:40.467
What-What-What's that, now?
Married?!

29:40.467 --> 29:42.367
No, no, no, Frank...
Frank, can I get you a shot?

29:42.367 --> 29:43.367
Veronica?

29:43.367 --> 29:44.300
Frank, it...

29:44.300 --> 29:45.500
Hey, Jess!

29:45.500 --> 29:47.300
(slurring):
Roll out the champagne!

29:47.300 --> 29:49.166
Our boy here is getting hitched!

29:49.166 --> 29:50.166
What?!

29:50.166 --> 29:51.633
Kev is marrying Veronica!

29:51.633 --> 29:54.400
Frank!
Carol! Carol!

29:54.400 --> 29:55.700
Carol, come here!

29:55.700 --> 29:57.166
No, no, Frank... Frank...
Carol, where are you?

29:57.166 --> 29:58.700
No, no, no, no,
no, no, no, Fr...

29:58.700 --> 30:00.300
Carol!
No, no, no, no, no! Frank!

30:00.300 --> 30:02.300
Kev's making an honest woman
out of your daughter!

30:02.300 --> 30:04.467
You what?!
Yeah!

30:04.467 --> 30:05.533
CAROL: Oh, my God!
(laughing)

30:05.533 --> 30:06.734
And to think I was
over there, drinking,

30:06.734 --> 30:08.467
worried about
that missing boy.

30:08.467 --> 30:10.734
Who gives a shit
about that now?
Hey!

30:10.734 --> 30:13.400
My daughter's getting married!
Kev's getting married
to Veronica!

30:13.400 --> 30:15.233
(all whooping, yelling)

30:15.233 --> 30:18.300
And I got the oldest
bottle of Asti Spumanti!

30:18.300 --> 30:20.633
Oh!

30:20.633 --> 30:24.500
You have made me... the
happiest woman in the world.

30:24.500 --> 30:26.066
I'm gonna go call Veronica.

30:26.066 --> 30:27.066
Wait, wait! No.

30:27.066 --> 30:28.300
She'll want to call you.

30:28.300 --> 30:29.533
You don't want
to ruin the surprise.

30:29.533 --> 30:31.100
Okay, everybody,

30:31.100 --> 30:32.500
drinks on the house!

30:32.500 --> 30:33.767
(cheering, whistling, whooping)

30:33.767 --> 30:37.033
Here you go--
one for the mama!

30:37.033 --> 30:38.166
There you go!

30:38.166 --> 30:40.133
All right, one for the
big daddy-- now for the mama.

30:40.133 --> 30:41.767
There we go!

30:41.767 --> 30:42.767
Yeah!

31:06.367 --> 31:08.333
(slurping loudly)

31:08.333 --> 31:10.767
(straw squeaking)

31:10.767 --> 31:13.400
Fiona Gallagher?!

31:13.400 --> 31:16.367
Yeah. Yeah, what about her?

31:16.367 --> 31:17.533
Nothing.

31:17.533 --> 31:18.567
Good.

31:18.567 --> 31:20.233
(straw squeaks)

31:20.233 --> 31:22.000
(slurps)

31:22.000 --> 31:23.300
(straw squeaks)

31:23.300 --> 31:25.734
You really wanna
hook up with her?

31:25.734 --> 31:27.467
A lot of kids over there, man.

31:27.467 --> 31:29.400
You're kidding, right?

31:29.400 --> 31:30.767
Your marriage only
lasted six weeks.

31:30.767 --> 31:31.667
Seven.

31:31.667 --> 31:33.266
And she wound up
with the house.

31:33.266 --> 31:35.533
My car's paid off!

31:35.533 --> 31:38.400
You giving me advice
is ridiculous.

31:38.400 --> 31:41.734
(slurping)

31:50.000 --> 31:52.000
(sucking silently)

31:55.400 --> 31:57.767
(TV newscast playing
indistinctly)

31:57.767 --> 31:59.433
Fiona...

31:59.433 --> 32:03.100
what a pleasant surprise.

32:05.133 --> 32:06.633
So they haven't
found him yet?

32:06.633 --> 32:08.400
(sighs heavily)

32:08.400 --> 32:09.734
I can't stop
thinking about

32:09.734 --> 32:12.433
what his parents
must be going through.

32:12.433 --> 32:14.700
I know.

32:14.700 --> 32:16.767
(sighs sadly)

32:18.333 --> 32:20.533
Do you want a drink?

32:20.533 --> 32:22.533
I've got a lot of booze.

32:22.533 --> 32:24.000
No mixers.

32:24.000 --> 32:25.567
Cup of coffee would be great.

32:28.367 --> 32:29.767
Why don't I make it?

32:31.133 --> 32:34.100
Oh, don't mind me.

32:34.100 --> 32:38.367
I accidentally took three
of my pills instead of one.

32:38.367 --> 32:41.633
(newscast continuing
indistinctly)

32:41.633 --> 32:43.600
Hey, wait a second...

32:45.166 --> 32:46.367
Hiya, mister.

32:46.367 --> 32:47.767
Hey, there.

32:50.100 --> 32:53.066
How about giving me
a big hug?

32:57.734 --> 32:59.233
(marker squeaking)

33:00.633 --> 33:03.500
I'm gonna blush,
and then they'll know!

33:03.500 --> 33:05.333
I can't be a nurse.
I'm not patient.

33:05.333 --> 33:06.600
I hate bedpans.

33:06.600 --> 33:08.033
I can't walk in clogs.

33:08.033 --> 33:10.333
And let's face it,
I'm too small!

33:13.467 --> 33:14.633
Peek-a-boo!

33:17.767 --> 33:20.200
Peek-a-boo...
Oh, my God!

33:25.633 --> 33:26.600
Mommy!

33:26.600 --> 33:28.533
Casey's back!

33:28.533 --> 33:30.100
I don't believe it!

33:30.100 --> 33:31.500
Is it him?
Mommy!

33:31.500 --> 33:33.233
It is!

33:33.233 --> 33:34.100
He's back.

33:37.400 --> 33:39.667
(sobbing) My baby!

33:39.667 --> 33:43.633
Where have you been?
We've been worried
sick about you!

33:43.633 --> 33:45.233
Where did you find him?

33:45.233 --> 33:46.667
He was walking all by himself.

33:46.667 --> 33:48.433
I didn't know where he lived.

33:48.433 --> 33:49.533
Thank you.
You're an angel.

33:49.533 --> 33:50.633
I don't, I don't...

33:50.633 --> 33:52.700
I don't know how
to thank you.

33:52.700 --> 33:54.500
Uh, here, just, uh...

33:54.500 --> 33:56.467
Here, take-take
all-- take it.

33:56.467 --> 33:58.100
Take all of it.
Just take everything.

33:58.100 --> 34:02.300
Thank you.
Thank you.

34:02.300 --> 34:04.033
I told you we'd find him.

34:04.033 --> 34:06.734
My Debbie found him!
A Gallagher saved the day!

34:06.734 --> 34:08.333
You bunch of losers.

34:11.400 --> 34:12.300
Bye!

34:16.033 --> 34:17.734
That's Deb's.

34:17.734 --> 34:21.000
No, I-I'm just helping her.

34:21.000 --> 34:25.000
Hey! You're on my hand.
You're...

34:26.600 --> 34:29.000
All right, I am your father.

34:29.000 --> 34:31.100
Hey, Deb. Good job.

34:31.100 --> 34:33.333
Fiona, you want to come
with us, please?

34:33.333 --> 34:34.433
Where?

34:34.433 --> 34:36.000
We need to take Deb
to the station.

34:36.000 --> 34:37.567
What for?

34:37.567 --> 34:39.400
We need to take a statement.

34:39.400 --> 34:41.667
Well, she-she found him.

34:41.667 --> 34:43.500
I mean, isn't that enough?

34:43.500 --> 34:45.200
We need a statement.

34:45.200 --> 34:46.600
You can stay with her.

34:46.600 --> 34:50.266
Nurse Debbie can handle it.

34:50.266 --> 34:52.166
What I'm trying
to tell you is

34:52.166 --> 34:58.500
that I have never seen
her love anybody--

34:58.500 --> 35:01.233
I mean, anybody--

35:01.233 --> 35:05.567
Oh...
no-- anybody as much
as she loves you.

35:05.567 --> 35:06.567
For real?

35:06.567 --> 35:07.600
I'm for real.

35:07.600 --> 35:10.266
Including her daddy.

35:10.266 --> 35:12.066
No!
Mm-hmm.

35:12.066 --> 35:13.667
Come on.

35:13.667 --> 35:18.567
Ooh, and honey,
she love him... Mm!

35:18.567 --> 35:22.433
Whoo! Mm-mmm.

35:24.633 --> 35:27.567
Oh, shit.

35:36.133 --> 35:37.433
V!

35:37.433 --> 35:39.367
V!

35:42.166 --> 35:44.400
V!

35:44.400 --> 35:46.767
V!

35:46.767 --> 35:49.133
Can you hear me?

35:49.133 --> 35:50.500
I need to speak
to Veronica Fisher.

35:50.500 --> 35:52.400
What the hell?!

35:55.667 --> 35:57.000
What are you doing?

35:57.000 --> 35:59.066
I'm here
to tell you something.

35:59.066 --> 36:02.367
I mean, I need
to ask you something.

36:02.367 --> 36:05.100
How did you get so drunk in
the middle of the afternoon?

36:09.567 --> 36:12.767
Veronica Fisher, will you do me
the honor of being my wife?

36:12.767 --> 36:15.734
Yes! Yeah!

36:15.734 --> 36:18.200
(Kevin groans)

36:18.200 --> 36:19.633
I love you, baby.

36:19.633 --> 36:21.533
I love you!
(laughs)

36:22.767 --> 36:24.500
I first saw him on Southport.

36:24.500 --> 36:27.233
He caught my eye because my baby
brother Liam loves Superman.

36:27.233 --> 36:28.200
After I noticed

36:28.200 --> 36:30.233
he was alone,
I took his hand.

36:30.233 --> 36:32.200
He's a very good walker

36:32.200 --> 36:33.433
and very well-mannered
for a toddler.

36:33.433 --> 36:36.400
I thought for sure someone
would let me use their phone.

36:36.400 --> 36:38.734
You know, I'm just so shocked
at the lack of humanity.

36:38.734 --> 36:40.100
Yes, I'd love a cookie.

36:40.100 --> 36:43.033
I remember Grand Avenue
from my Aunt Ginger.

36:43.033 --> 36:44.400
Do they require you

36:44.400 --> 36:47.567
to wear a jacket and tie
or is that your choice?

36:47.567 --> 36:49.100
I find it very fetching!

37:03.533 --> 37:05.133
Big day.

37:05.133 --> 37:06.767
Yeah.

37:06.767 --> 37:08.266
Happy ending.

37:09.500 --> 37:11.567
Yep.

37:11.567 --> 37:15.467
You missed
a good pot roast last week.

37:15.467 --> 37:18.266
My mom really
pulled out all the stops.

37:20.066 --> 37:22.266
Yeah...

37:22.266 --> 37:24.266
I'm sorry about that.

37:34.266 --> 37:35.734
KAREN:
That's so great

37:35.734 --> 37:37.700
about Debbie finding
that little Casey.

37:37.700 --> 37:39.233
Yeah, I know.

37:39.233 --> 37:42.600
He was lucky it was her
and not some crazy fucker.

37:42.600 --> 37:44.467
I like
your new jeans.

37:44.467 --> 37:45.700
Oh, thanks.

37:45.700 --> 37:48.133
They didn't cheer me up
as much as I'd hoped.

37:48.133 --> 37:49.467
My house is
so fucking weird.

37:49.467 --> 37:51.166
I wish I'd been kidnapped.

37:51.166 --> 37:53.166
Is it that bad?

37:53.166 --> 37:55.033
Yeah. You should have
seen him at breakfast.

37:55.033 --> 37:57.333
I can't imagine
what dinners are
gonna be like.

37:57.333 --> 37:59.700
And, in fact,
as soon as he gets
down to the bottom,

37:59.700 --> 38:01.767
I look back and there are
all these people behind us,

38:01.767 --> 38:04.033
Yes.
and I start yelling,
"Go back! Go back!"

38:04.033 --> 38:06.033
Why? (laughs)

38:06.033 --> 38:07.333
Because he stepped
off of the thing,

38:07.333 --> 38:09.133
and he just stopped there.

38:09.133 --> 38:10.667
And there are all
of these people...

38:10.667 --> 38:12.100
Oh, thank you.

38:12.100 --> 38:15.200
You know, your house is
Frank's wet dream.

38:15.200 --> 38:18.233
Never gonna get
him out.

38:19.266 --> 38:21.066
Wanna sneak into
my backyard

38:21.066 --> 38:23.467
and do it on
the tire swing?

38:23.467 --> 38:25.200
Lip?

38:25.200 --> 38:26.667
Wait, I'm thinking.

38:26.667 --> 38:29.767
REPORTER (on TV):
Well, I guess sometimes
there are happy endings.

38:29.767 --> 38:31.533
Casey Casden, the little boy
who disappeared

38:31.533 --> 38:33.200
from his own front yard
earlier today

38:33.200 --> 38:37.467
has been delivered home
safe and sound.

38:37.467 --> 38:39.300
ANCHORMAN: Oh, thank you, Lisa.
That is indeed great, great...

38:39.300 --> 38:40.333
(whispering):
Fiona!

38:40.333 --> 38:43.100
♪ ♪

38:48.066 --> 38:50.000
What's up?

38:51.367 --> 38:53.333
Um, for Debbie.

38:55.734 --> 38:57.567
Okay. Mm-hmm.

39:01.100 --> 39:04.200
Hey, Debs, look
what Steve bought.

39:04.200 --> 39:05.367
Oh, my God!

39:05.367 --> 39:06.700
For me?

39:06.700 --> 39:08.233
Absolutely.

39:08.233 --> 39:09.667
For doing
such a great job today.

39:09.667 --> 39:10.767
Thank you!

39:10.767 --> 39:12.000
What you gonna name her?

39:12.000 --> 39:14.233
(laughing)
Gin-Gin.

39:14.233 --> 39:16.200
After Aunt Ginger.

39:16.200 --> 39:17.667
Let's go up to my room.
We can play!

39:17.667 --> 39:20.100
(laughing)

39:20.100 --> 39:22.667
Oh, Gin-Gin,
you're so funny.

39:22.667 --> 39:25.100
(Debbie giggling)

39:25.100 --> 39:27.300
DEBBIE:
Oh, Gin-Gin...

39:31.000 --> 39:33.266
(groans)

39:39.300 --> 39:41.233
VERONICA:
Kevin, wake up.

39:41.233 --> 39:43.400
It's time to get drunk again.

39:45.633 --> 39:48.533
$690, $700,

39:48.533 --> 39:53.200
$710, $715 exactly.

39:58.400 --> 40:00.433
Hmm... Ah.

40:00.433 --> 40:03.300
(keypad beeping)

40:03.300 --> 40:05.700
(groans)

40:05.700 --> 40:10.066
(sighs)

40:10.066 --> 40:11.734
Thanks for buying
her that doll.

40:11.734 --> 40:14.767
No. Not a problem.

40:14.767 --> 40:18.133
You know what would
feel great right now?

40:18.133 --> 40:21.133
Hmm?
A long, hot shower.

40:21.133 --> 40:23.033
I'll wash your back.

40:28.533 --> 40:31.400
Shit.

40:31.400 --> 40:33.467
No hot water.

40:36.166 --> 40:38.500
You really
are beautiful.

40:44.433 --> 40:47.300
I hope I'm not
fucking up the kids.

40:49.567 --> 40:51.300
VERONICA:
Fiona!

40:53.667 --> 40:56.700
Fiona, where are you?

40:56.700 --> 40:59.367
(laughing)

40:59.367 --> 41:00.567
Here.

41:00.567 --> 41:02.467
Fiona!

41:02.467 --> 41:04.333
Yeah!

41:04.333 --> 41:06.000
Mommy!

41:06.000 --> 41:08.066
(laughing)

41:08.066 --> 41:10.166
What the hell?
Champagne?

41:10.166 --> 41:12.333
I'm getting married.

41:12.333 --> 41:14.400
Oh, my God!

41:14.400 --> 41:16.200
(all cheering)

41:16.200 --> 41:18.333
(music blaring)

41:22.200 --> 41:25.333
(everyone talking, laughing)

41:30.266 --> 41:32.133
She's great.

41:32.133 --> 41:34.066
Yeah, man.

41:34.066 --> 41:35.233
She's a good egg.

41:35.233 --> 41:37.333
She deserves it.

41:37.333 --> 41:39.667
Yeah, but does she
deserve you, you bastard?

41:39.667 --> 41:41.333
(chuckles)

41:41.333 --> 41:44.367
No. Nobody does.

42:05.367 --> 42:06.767
Take the Advil now.

42:06.767 --> 42:09.166
You want to stay
ahead of the pain.

42:10.633 --> 42:12.700
(sighs)

42:14.433 --> 42:18.166
(music blaring over
indistinct conversation)

42:23.233 --> 42:25.433
(laughter,
conversation continue)

42:27.000 --> 42:29.133
Penny for your
thoughts.

42:29.133 --> 42:30.300
Really, Grandma?

42:30.300 --> 42:31.533
I know.

42:31.533 --> 42:35.066
I'm a 60-year-old lady
with the vaj of a newborn.

42:35.066 --> 42:37.066
(spluttering laugh)

42:37.066 --> 42:38.066
(laughing)

42:40.266 --> 42:42.200
You know I love you
guys, right, Kev?

42:42.200 --> 42:44.266
I couldn't raise these
kids without you and V.

42:44.266 --> 42:46.200
I know they borrow
your shit all the time.

42:46.200 --> 42:47.300
I'm sorry.
I know it's lame.

42:47.300 --> 42:49.533
But thanks. (kisses)

42:49.533 --> 42:51.667
I don't know how I'd do it
without you guys.

42:51.667 --> 42:53.266
And I just
love you so much.

42:53.266 --> 42:55.000
I'm just so happy
for you both.

42:55.000 --> 42:56.200
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

42:56.200 --> 42:58.200
You know that Jagermeister
really makes you chatty.

42:58.200 --> 43:00.033
Right? You know that?

43:00.033 --> 43:03.066
(laughing)

43:03.066 --> 43:04.400
Look at V.

43:04.400 --> 43:07.300
Isn't she beautiful?

43:07.300 --> 43:10.633
Yeah... She sure is.

43:10.633 --> 43:12.567
(beeping in distance)

43:15.033 --> 43:16.567
What the hell is that?

43:21.433 --> 43:22.633
Debbie?

43:29.567 --> 43:31.700
It's our new
water heater.

43:31.700 --> 43:33.066
I got it on sale.

43:33.066 --> 43:34.066
(all laughing)

43:34.066 --> 43:36.233
And free delivery.

43:36.233 --> 43:37.734
He said
because I'm a hero.

43:37.734 --> 43:40.100
You are my girl!

43:40.100 --> 43:42.100
Oh, man.

43:42.100 --> 43:45.200
You're gonna go to the back and
you're gonna make a sharp left.

43:45.200 --> 43:47.033
And install it in the kitchen.

43:47.033 --> 43:49.700
Take it in the kitchen.
Go straight down.

43:49.700 --> 43:54.700
DEBBIE: By the way, I
call the first hot shower.

43:54.700 --> 43:57.100
That was something, huh?

43:57.100 --> 43:58.734
Yeah.

44:01.333 --> 44:03.467
You know, for a guy
who just got engaged,

44:03.467 --> 44:05.633
you don't seem very happy
to be getting married.

44:09.333 --> 44:11.500
That's 'cause
I'm already married.

44:56.767 --> 44:59.467
Debs, you've got
to get ready for school.

44:59.467 --> 45:02.700
I can't go to school.

45:02.700 --> 45:04.533
Why not?

